title: Frank Zappa -- We're Only In It For the Money & L
description:
This is the remix of the album, unlike the original release or the current version available through Rhino records.  It features the unexpurgated lyrics and is a definite must for any Zappa fan.  This album sounds completely different and this version has new songs that the others do not --

(1)  Are You Hung Up?

(2)  Who Needs the Peace Corps?

(3)  Concentration Moon

(4)  Mom & Dad

(5)  Telephone Conversation

(6)  Bow Tie Daddy

(7)  Harry, You\&#039;re a Beast (uncensored)

(8)  What\&#039;s the Ugliest Part of Your Body?

(9)  Absolutely Free

(10)  Flower Punk

(11)  Hot Poop

(12)  Nasal Retentive Calliope Music

(13)  Let\&#039;s Make the Water Turn Black

(14)  The Idiot Bastard Son

(15)  Lonely Little Girl

(16)  Take Your Clothes Off When You Dance

(17)  What\&#039;s the Ugliest Part of Your Body (reprise)?

(18)  Mother People

(19)  The Chrome-Plated Megaphone of Destiny

(20)  Lumpy Gravy I

(21)  Lumpy Gravy II


If you don\&#039;t download and listen to this album, you aren\&#039;t a Frank Zappa fan, plain and simple.
